text: very surprised by their sambal fried rice. i was having a hard time deciding whether i should get a sweet and sour fish bento with egg fried rice or sambal fried rice when ordering and the super helpful Faizul broke down the taste profile for me and safe to say his recommendation was really good! all my family members liked the combination. please look for Faizul if you’re having a hard time deciding what to get. he made the best recommendation! 10/10 no notes. ps i didnt get to take a picture of the food bc everyone dug in so thats all u get, sorry if it looks messy but thats when you know the food is gooood
Many stalls to choose. Spoil for choice. Western to Lontong to chicken rice/ ayam penyet to Indian prata . Operates early as 6am. Plenty open HDB car parks.
Last week..1st time I lunch in ..today 2nd I taken my supper..so many choices of food & drinks..price was reasonable & affordable ..near to Al-Mukminin mosque jurong east
Always a go to place when having family dinner once in a while. Wide varieties of food selection from western-indian-asian ❤️
A lot of food choices and most are delicious! Place is clean, good ambience. food prices can be quite pricey
